title: Grateful Dead Live at Frost Amphitheatre on 1982-10-10
description:
Set 1

Minglewood Blues-> Sugaree-> Little Red Rooster, Tennessee Jed, Cassidy, Loser, Far From Me, Looks Like Rain-> China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider

Set 2

Playin' In The Band-> Crazy Fingers-> Lost Sailor-> Saint Of Circumstance-> Touch Of Gray-> Drums-> The Wheel-> Throwing Stones-> Not Fade Away-> Black Peter-> Sugar Magnolia, E:Satisfaction-> E: It's All Over Now Baby Blue

reviews.review_text: Monster Upgrade! Fantastic job Hunter Seamons! This is as crystal clear audio as if George Lucas remastered this at ILM or THX for a star wars movie. Fun show (i love 82, and i don't care what anyone says!).  Check out the china->rider, the early years uptempo touch, a soulful black peter, and of course bobby's cheeseball Mick Jagger impersonation on satisfaction. That will keep me smiling all day.  Great job on the sound.

Wow. Just wow.... Man, thanks so much for this upgrade - the quality is astoundingly good. I'm mostly a 70's era guy, but I think this is my favourite 80's show. I mean, what a great setlist, and great playing too. The only way this show could be any better (for me) is if they had slipped in a Shakedown in that second set. Keep up the great work - I love your mixes.

Headphone gold The soundboard of this show never had the sparkle to back up the great performance. This matrix fixes that problem and then some. Listen on a pair of quality headphones, the feel of the room is excellent.
As for the show itself, it's one of those ones where you can tell they legitimately give a shit and have fun from start to end.

Frosted Freaks Love the nice warm sound of this Matrix..beautiful head candy,But what really hit me with this show is the solid 1st set and A monster 2nd set..Playin'>Crazy Fingers>Sailor>Saint>Touch..Wooo Hoooo~! And a nice double encore of Satisfaction>Baby Blue~~~GIVE IT A WHRL>Forever Dead>Forever Grateful
Prime ‘82 Fantastic sound on a fantastic show. ‘82 is criminally underrated.
